data.message:
saying:
var x = new { Name = "Derp", Age = 99 };
is not a dynamic type, it's an anonymous type! The class definition is created by the compiler for you and t stays that way throughout the runtime of your program (and thus it's staticly typed), IF you could add a new property to x (like with ExpandoObject) or change the type of 'x' later during runtime (if you said dynamic instead of var), then it would be called dynamic typing :)
